               <p>ANTHONY BOUSFIELD. I am a <rs id="t18281023-159-viclabel948" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-159-victim872 t18281023-159-viclabel948"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281023-159-crimeloc949">Great Marlborough-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-159-crimeloc949" type="placeName" value="Great Marlborough-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-159-crimeloc949" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-159-off946 t18281023-159-crimeloc949"></join>. I lost a pair of steps on the 2d of October, from outside my window, a little after five o'clock in the evening; I did not know they were gone till I saw them in possession of the officer - I had seen them safe about three quarters of an hour before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-159-person873">
                  GEORGE 
                  AVIS
               <interp inst="t18281023-159-person873" type="surname" value="AVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-159-person873" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-159-person873" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and live in Tyler's-court. I was coming home about five o'clock that evening, and saw the prisoner standing with his back against these steps; I got to my own door, and saw him just behind me, with them - I stopped him, and told him he must go back with me; he said he was glad he was taken, for he had been out of a situation, walking all day, and was tired and hungry.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was actually starving.</p>
               <p>
